parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake actuator assembly can cause the brake pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake booster pump can cause the brake pedal to become hard to press, leading to increased stopping distances, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal is hard to press
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to lose traction, leading to increased stopping distances, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The ABS warning light is illuminated
the brake system warning light is illuminated

the vehicle's stability control system is disabled
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual.

lack of awareness of the potential defect
